		<item>
			<title>Annie Di Donna</title>
			<link>http://www.logicomix.com/en/index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=81:annie-di-donna&amp;catid=37:the-team&amp;Itemid=18</link>
			<guid>http://www.logicomix.com/en/index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=81:annie-di-donna&amp;catid=37:the-team&amp;Itemid=18</guid>
			<description><![CDATA[<p><a target="_blank" href="http://www.logicomix.com/en/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=81:annie-di-donna&catid=37:2008-12-26-20-19-16&Itemid=18"><img style="float: left;" alt="team4-small" src="http://www.logicomix.com/en/images/stories/theTeam/team4-small.jpg" height="98" width="98" /></a><span style="font-size: 11pt;"><span style="color: #993300;"><a href="http://www.logicomix.com/en/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=81:annie-di-donna&catid=37:2008-12-26-20-19-16&Itemid=18">Annie Di Donna</a></span></span> - color<br /><br />Annie studied painting in France.  She worked in animation for twenty years before coming to comics.  When she’s not drawing, she tells us, she likes to “dance ze night away”.</p>
]]></description>
			<author>info@intelweb.gr (Vaggelis)</author>
