		<item>
			<title>Alecos Papadatos</title>
			<link>http://www.logicomix.com/en/index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=80:alecos-papadatos&amp;catid=37:the-team&amp;Itemid=18</link>
			<guid>http://www.logicomix.com/en/index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=80:alecos-papadatos&amp;catid=37:the-team&amp;Itemid=18</guid>
			<description><![CDATA[<p><a target="_self" href="http://www.logicomix.com/en/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=80:2008-12-29-09-38-33&catid=37:2008-12-26-20-19-16&Itemid=18"><img src="http://www.logicomix.com/en/images/stories/theTeam/team3-small.jpg" alt="team3-small" style="float: left;" width="98" height="98" /></a> <span style="font-size: 11pt;"><span style="color: #993300;"><a href="http://www.logicomix.com/en/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=80:2008-12-29-09-38-33&catid=37:2008-12-26-20-19-16&Itemid=18">Alecos Papadatos</a></span></span> - character design and drawings<br /><br />After working in animation for twenty years, Alecos turned from moving images to his childhood love of stationary ones: comics. After a long day’s work, Alecos likes to kick back and play his bouzouki. <span style="font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva;"></span></p>
]]></description>
			<author>info@intelweb.gr (Vaggelis)</author>
			<category>The Team</category>
			<pubDate>Mon, 29 Dec 2008 09:37:54 +0000</pubDate>
